<p><strong><span style="font-size: 16px;">1. First step</span></strong></p>
<p>First, we need to tell the dynamic grid that we're going to use attributes:<br />
<br />
</p>
<pre>&lt;Results&gt;
&nbsp; &lt;UseAttributes&gt;1&lt;/UseAttributes&gt;
&lt;/Results&gt;
</pre>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 16px;">2. Item template</span></strong></p>
<p>
Later on, we need to provide an item template.<br />
The item template defines columns that are going to be used in the dynamic grid. Every column can specify a set of properties that will be applied for every row, if not overwritten by this row.<br />
<br />
</p>
<pre>&lt;Results&gt;
&nbsp; &lt;UseAttributes&gt;1&lt;/UseAttributes&gt;
<strong>&nbsp; &lt;ItemTemplate&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attributes&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attribute ColumnCode="Name" HeaderText="Name" /&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attribute ColumnCode="Status" HeaderText="Status" /&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attribute ColumnCode="StartDate" HeaderText="Start Date" /&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attribute ColumnCode="EndDate" HeaderText="End Date" /&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;/Attributes&gt;
&nbsp; &lt;/ItemTemplate&gt;</strong>
&lt;/Results&gt;</pre>
<br />
The dynamic grid generated based on the xml above won't show any content as there are no rows added.<br />
Let's add an empty row to see any result.<br />
<br />
<pre>&lt;Results&gt;
&nbsp; &lt;UseAttributes&gt;1&lt;/UseAttributes&gt;
&nbsp; &lt;ItemTemplate&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attributes&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attribute ColumnCode="Name" HeaderText="Name" /&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attribute ColumnCode="Status" HeaderText="Status" /&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attribute ColumnCode="StartDate" HeaderText="Start Date" /&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attribute ColumnCode="EndDate" HeaderText="End Date" /&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;/Attributes&gt;
&nbsp; &lt;/ItemTemplate&gt;
<strong>&nbsp; &lt;RootItem&gt;
&nbsp; <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">	</span>&lt;Attributes&gt;
&nbsp; <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">	</span>&lt;/Attributes&gt;
&nbsp; &lt;/RootItem&gt;</strong>
&lt;/Results&gt;
</pre>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 16px;">3. Filling with data</span></strong></p>
<p>
We'll now provide some values for our row.<br />
<br />
We do that by creating "Attribute" nodes. Each "Attribute" node has to have ColumnCode corresponding to one of the column codes from the item template.<br />
In each of these "Attribute" nodes you can specify a group of properties that you want to apply just for this column and just for this row (so, in fact, just for this one cell).<br />
These properties will overwrite the properties set in the item template, if any.<br />
<span style="color: #ff0000;"><br />
NOTE: You don't need to create an "Attribute" node for every column in the item template - just for the ones you want to provide additional / overwritten values to.</span><br />
<br />
So, let's say that I want to have a row of name "First product", status "Completed" with a blue border and start date as a date picker set to "23/06/2016".<br />
I also want to have every row in my dynamic grid to have end date as a date picker with the value set to "31/12/2016". In order to see clearly that this works I'll create one more empty row.<br />
<br />
The above can be achieved with the following xml:<br />
<br />
</p>
<pre>&lt;Results&gt;
&nbsp; &lt;UseAttributes&gt;1&lt;/UseAttributes&gt;
&nbsp; &lt;ItemTemplate&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attributes&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attribute ColumnCode="Name" HeaderText="Name" /&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attribute ColumnCode="Status" HeaderText="Status" /&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attribute ColumnCode="StartDate" HeaderText="Start Date" /&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;Attribute ColumnCode="EndDate" HeaderText="End Date" <strong>ControlType="DatePicker" Value="31-12-2016"</strong> /&gt;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;/Attributes&gt;
&nbsp; &lt;/ItemTemplate&gt;
<strong>&nbsp; &lt;RootItem&gt;
&nbsp; <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">	</span>&lt;Attributes&gt;
&nbsp; <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">	</span> &nbsp;&lt;Attribute ColumnCode="Name" Value="First product" /&gt;
&nbsp; <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">	</span> &nbsp;&lt;Attribute ColumnCode="Status" Value="Completed" BorderColour="Blue" /&gt;
&nbsp; <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">	</span> &nbsp;&lt;Attribute ColumnCode="StartDate" ControlType="DatePicker" Value="23-06-2016" /&gt;
&nbsp; <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">	</span>&lt;/Attributes&gt;
&nbsp; &lt;/RootItem&gt;
&nbsp; &lt;RootItem&gt;
&nbsp; <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">	</span>&lt;Attributes&gt;
&nbsp; <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">	</span>&lt;/Attributes&gt;
&nbsp; &lt;/RootItem&gt;</strong>
&lt;/Results&gt;</pre>
